properties.headline: SCHEDULED ROADWORK Intersection upgrade - LAKE INNES (SOUTH OF PORT MACQUARIE) Pacific Highway at Houston Mitchell Drive, Lake Innes
properties.adviceB: Check signage; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Right hand turns into and out of Houston Mitchell Drive will be restricted while work continues on the intersection upgrade.

Motorists wanting to travel north from Houston Mitchell Drive will need turn left to travel south along the Pacific Highway to Bago Road interchange at Herons Creek before turning north, approximately 7.5km one way.

Alternatively, motorists travelling to Port Macquarie from Bonny Hills can use Ocean Drive.

Northbound motorists accessing Bonny Hills from the Pacific Highway should exit at Ocean Drive interchange at Kew (approximately 15km south of Houston Mitchell Drive) and travel via Laurieton and North Haven.

An alternative route for northbound motorists accessing Bonny Hills from the Pacific Highway is via the Port Macquarie interchange (intersection of the Pacific Highway and Oxley Highway) where they can perform a U-turn to travel south along the Pacific Highway and turn left into Houston Mitchell Drive.

Southbound motorists will be able to access Bonny Hills from the Pacific Highway at all times, however are likely to encounter traffic control during work hours.

Cyclists will also be restricted from right hand turns into and out of Houston Mitchell Drive and travelling southbound on the Pacific Highway beyond Ryans Road. A cyclist movement plan will be in place during work.

Some night work may be required on occasion.
